# TwinCAT Offline InfoSys MSHC Lookup

## Available MCP Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `twincat_infosys_mshc_search` | Search local offline InfoSys documentation for types, attributes, articles |
| `twincat_infosys_mshc_read` | Read a specific page with structured content extraction |

## When to Use

- Looking up the exact signature (VAR_INPUT/VAR_OUTPUT) of a Beckhoff FB, STRUCT, ENUM, or FUNCTION
- Checking attribute pragma syntax (`pack_mode`, `strict`, `TcRpcEnable`, `hide`, etc.)
- Finding which library a type belongs to (Tc3_IotBase, Tc2_System, etc.)
- Verifying method names and descriptions for a FUNCTION_BLOCK
- Any InfoSys documentation lookup — **prefer offline over web search**

## Quick Lookup Pattern

For most lookups, a single search call with `auto_read=true` (default) is sufficient:

```
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="FB_IotMqttClient")
twincat_infosys_mshc_search(query="FB_IotMqttClient", language="de")
```

When the top result scores 100, the full page content is automatically included as `auto_read` in the response. No separate `twincat_infosys_mshc_read` call needed.

## Language Support

| `language` | Documentation | Section headers | Description language |
|------------|---------------|-----------------|---------------------|
| `"en"` (default) | English (EN-US) | Inputs, Outputs, Methods | English |
| `"de"` | German (DE-DE) | Eingänge, Ausgänge, Methoden | German |

Both languages share the same page IDs — only the language subfolder differs (`/1033/` vs `/1031/`).

## Search Tips

- Type names (FB_, ST_, E_) are identical in both languages
- For **attribute pragmas**: search by attribute name: `pack_mode`, `strict`, `noinit` — in DE docs use German titles: `Attribut 'pack_mode'`
- For **methods of an FB**: read the parent FB page — methods are listed in the `methods` field
- For **content search**: use `mode="fulltext"` explicitly — slower but searches inside page HTML
- For **typed symbols only**: use `mode="symbol"` to filter to FB_/ST_/E_/I_/F_ prefixes

## Response Structure

The `auto_read` or `twincat_infosys_mshc_read` response contains:

- `syntax`: Full ST declaration block (FB/STRUCT/ENUM) or usage example (attributes)
- `inputs[]`: `{name, type, description}` — for FBs, STRUCTs
- `outputs[]`: `{name, type, description}` — for FBs
- `methods[]`: `{name, description}` — for FBs
- `requirements`: `{twincat_version, library}`
- `description`: Short summary from HTML meta tag
- `full_text`: **Complete page text** (HTML stripped) — always present, also for articles, attribute pages, guides, and any non-FB content

## Prefer Offline Over Web

Always use `twincat_infosys_mshc_search` before falling back to `WebSearch` + `WebFetch` for InfoSys lookups. The offline tool is faster, returns structured data, and works without internet.
